    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="956"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d956">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 356.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 8th instant I sent you the following
                        telegram.<note n="1" xml:id="d956fn1">Printed ante.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The instruction referred to is No. 352 of the 2d instant. I inclose herewith for
                    your information a copy of a telegram,<note n="1" xml:id="d956fn2">Printed
                        ante.</note> dated the 7th instant, from Minister Corea, on which the
                    telegram to you was based, together with a copy of my note<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d956fn3">Printed ante.</note> to him in reply.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
